CM_ BO_ 290 "IGNITION SWITCH COMMANDS  stored in the first word  $00000000 – off $00010000 – off $03010000 – engine kill $03020000 – engine kill $05020000 – accessory on $15020000 – accessory on $44010000 – remote run (on) $44020000 – normal run (on) $45010000 – start command recv’d $5d010000 – starter is cranking  There may be additional values yet to be discovered. It is not known why there are two “off” and “engine kill” values.  * this location is highly useful in many different applications *";
CM_ BO_ 299 "UNKNOWN  $xx – bitmap, byte  You can use this presence of this message (ID 12B with only 1 byte of data) to confirm that you’re reading data from the CAN-IHS bus.";
CM_ BO_ 448 "REMOTE CONTROL COMMANDS  $000000800000 – none (idle) $210000900000 – keyfob lock $230000900000 - 1st press fob unlock $240000900000 - 2nd press fob unlock $2E0000900000 – keyfob panic button $410000800000 – unknown $430000800000 – driver keyless entry $5B0000800000 – unknown $6A0000800000 – (any) cancel rem start $690000800000 – keyfob remote start $810000880000 – app lock doors $830000880000 – app unlock doors $830000880000 – app panic button  can-c should be used to send vehicle commands. stat";
CM_ BO_ 456 "UNKNOWN – KEYFOB RELATED  Personal keyfob id? Keyless Entry / Remote Start";
CM_ BO_ 557 "STEERING WHEEL BUTTONS FOR AUDIO CONTROLS  (unverified / incomplete)  00 00 00 01=right arrow 00 00 00 04=up arrow 00 00 10 00=left arrow 00 00 40 00=down arrow";
CM_ BO_ 559 "VEHICLE STATUS (MAY REQUIRE REMOTE START)  $xx – status byte";
CM_ BO_ 562 "AXLE DISTANCE TRAVELED UNKNOWN TEMPERATURE,  $??xx???????? – unknown, temp? $????xxxx???? -- distance 1 $????????xxxx – distance 2  Similar values found at id $0DD";
CM_ BO_ 579 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $000000000000 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: (none)";
CM_ BO_ 584 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $0000FFFFFF03FFFF Wrangler 2: $0000FFFFFF03FFFF Wrangler 3: $0000FFFFFF03FFFF";
CM_ BO_ 590 "FRONT AXLE FORCE SENSORS?  appears to be road feedback information for the front and rear axles. combines with data from $252.";
CM_ BO_ 594 "REAR AXLE FORCE SENSORS?  appears to be road feedback information for the front and rear axles. combines with data from $24E";
CM_ BO_ 627 "AC FAN & TUNER UP / DOWN BUTTONS  $00000A0000000000 fan down $0000050000000000 fan up $0000090000000000 fan up also?! $???????????????? tune up [TBD] $???????????????? tune down [TBD}";
CM_ BO_ 685 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $003C030000000003 Wrangler 2: $0000000000000000 Wrangler 3: $C001030000000000";
CM_ BO_ 690 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $FFFFFF000040FF00 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: (none)";
CM_ BO_ 706 "AUX BATTERY VOLTAGE AND UNKNOWN BYTE  $xxxx??00 – Unknown. Charge? Load? $????xx00 – aux battery 1/10th volts  NOTE: The unknown variable might be a temperature in 1/100th degrees C?";
CM_ BO_ 707 "UNKNOWN AXLE SPEED?  $xxxx????0000FF00 – value, word $????xxxx0000FF00 – value, word  Constantly increasing, apparently with vehicle movement. Wheel speed? Axle data?";
CM_ BO_ 709 "RADIO & CONNECTIVITY BITMAP Also see: Read by ID $0148 on the BCM  Wrangler 1: $01EEEE1C05000000 Wrangler 2: $01EEEE0C05000000 Wrangler 3: $01EEEE1805000000 ";
CM_ BO_ 710 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $4123062300000000 Wrangler 2: $4113010300000000 Wrangler 3: $4123051200000002";
CM_ BO_ 711 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $8108000000000000 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: (none)";
CM_ BO_ 723 "HVAC/RADIO/ESS/TRACTION BUTTONS  $0700000000000001 Traction control on/off $0700000000000040 Radio on/off $0700000000000100 A/C system on/off $0700000000000200 Air recirculation on/off $0700000000000800 HVAC vent mode $0700000000010000 HVAC sytem on/off $0700000000020000 Automatic HVAC control $0700000000040000 Driver temp + $0700000000080000 Driver temp - $0700000000100000 Passenger temp + $0700000000200000 Passenger temp - $0700000000400000 Rear defroster $0700000000800000 Front defroster $070";
CM_ BO_ 724 "HEATED SEATS / HEATED WHEEL BUTTONS  $0000010000000000 driver seat heater $0000100000000000 passenger seat heater $0040000000000000 steering wheel heater";
CM_ BO_ 736 "UNKNOWN  A rare bit flip seen in second byte";
CM_ BO_ 755 "UNKNOWN – MULTIPLE USES?  First byte reports if both the engine is running AND the driver’s seat belt is fastened.  $08=one or more exceptions $00=yes  If $08, will momentarily switch to $00 and back if you command the radio to sync the AC or turn climate off.";
CM_ BO_ 760 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $00FFF00000002800 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: $00FFF00000002800";
CM_ BO_ 762 "LIGHTS / LOCKS / DOORS  $xx?????????????? -- door opened value & 0x00=none opened value & 0x01=driver value & 0x02=passenger value & 0x04=rear driver value & 0x08=rear passenger value & 0x20=swing gate value & 0x2F=all five open value & 0x40=(secured?)  $???x???????????? -- parking lights $1=off $0=on  $????xx?????????? -- interior dimmer $22=dim $C8=bright  $??????xx???????? -- door lock button 00=all doors locked 18=all doors unlocked  There may be additional functions and values not yet docum";
CM_ BO_ 767 "Engine Oil Temp / Fuel Economy  $00xx????FFFFFFFF = Engine Oil Temp $00??xxxxFFFFFFFF = Fuel Economy   Second variable changes while driving. Range is from $0000 to $03FF.";
CM_ BO_ 769 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $0000000000000000 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: (none)";
CM_ BO_ 770 "UCONNECT CAMERA VIEW  $xxxx08000000 -- Camera View  uConnect camera view options: $0000 = offline $0002 = Reverse $0007 = Cargo Cam $0009 = initializing";
CM_ BO_ 773 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $FF00000000000000 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: (none)";
CM_ BO_ 774 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $0000000000002800 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: (none)";
CM_ BO_ 778 "TEMPERATURES  Wrangler 1: $048000xxFC0002?? -- temp1 Wrangler 2: $048000xxFC0002?? -- temp1 Wrangler 3: $008000xx200002?? -- Engine Coolant Temp ((($value / 100) - 40) * (5 / 9) + 32) Wrangler 1: $048000??FC0002xx -- temp2 Wrangler 2: $048000??FC0002xx -- temp2 Wrangler 3: $008000??200002xx -- Unknown  Behaves like temperature readings. What is being measured is unknown.";
CM_ BO_ 781 "RADIO AMPLIFIER  NAVIGATION VOICE VOLUME other volumes are likely";
CM_ BO_ 782 "UNKNOWN  Bitmap byte, variable byte, bitmap word?, static word, static word";
CM_ BO_ 783 "RADIO AMPLIFIER (VOLUME, EQUALIZER, ETC)  $??????????????xx -- speed adj volume 00=off, 02=level 1, 04=level 2, 06=level 3  [needs more bytes documented]";
CM_ BO_ 784 "SKY ONE-TOUCH STATUS (READ-ONLY)  $xx – sky one touch bitmap, byte  Reports back a bitmap encoding the position of the Sky One-Touch top (fully open, fully closed, or mid-position) and any control buttons pressed (open, close).";
CM_ BO_ 788 "WRITE-ONLY RADIO SETTINGS  This CAN ID is used to permanently store the user configuration settings that are only available through uConnect radio.  Configuration data is written using a method that is different from other CAN IDs. For a list of settings, please scroll right and read the comments field.  Currently, there is no known method of reading the current value of these same settings.  Use caution writing to these variables, as it may be difficult to undo any changes without knowing what ";
CM_ BO_ 791 "UNKNOWN  $0000000000xx??00 – unknown $0000000000??xx00 – unknown";
CM_ BO_ 792 "STEERING WHEEL CONTROLS  $x????? -- right steering wheel stalk 1=momentary front wiper active 2=momentary front windshield mist sprayer  $?x???? -- left steering wheel stalk 1=left turn signal active 2=right turn signal active 4=high beams toggled on 8=momentary high beams on  $???x?? -- rear windshield wiper 1=slow rear windshield wiper 2=momentary rear windshield mist sprayer 3=fast rear windshield wiper  $?????x -- front windshield wiper 1,2,3,4,D,E=windshield wiper speed settings  STEERING W";
CM_ BO_ 798 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $008000C00000 Wrangler 1: $018000C00000 Wrangler 1: $028000C00000 Wrangler 1: $038000C00000 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: $008000C00000";
CM_ BO_ 802 "ENGINE RPMs AND VEHICLE ACTUAL MPH  $xxxx??????ff – actual engine RPMs $????xxxx??ff – actual vehicle MPH x 200 $????????xxff – unknown variable (byte)  This version of the vehicle's speed should be determined based upon tire size and gearing, not corrected using GPS data.";
CM_ BO_ 808 "EVIC MUSIC INFO DISPLAY  Controls the artist, album, and title which is displayed on the EVIC's screen for music info";
CM_ BO_ 810 "UNITS OF MEASUREMENT  $????????????0810 – metric default $????????????d82b – us imperial default  For custom options, use bitmap:  UNITS FOR TEMPERATURE: $????????????0??? – degrees c $????????????8??? – degrees f UNITS FOR GAS MILEAGE: $?????????????0?? – km/L $?????????????8?? – L/100km $????????????10?? – UK MPG $????????????18?? – US MPG UNITS FOR PRESSURE: $??????????????0? – kpa $??????????????1? – bar $??????????????2? – psi UNITS FOR DISTANCE: $???????????????0 – kilometers $????????????";
CM_ BO_ 815 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $FF0000 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: $000000";
CM_ BO_ 818 "HVAC FAN STATUS / Outside Temp  Sensing of AC fan motor speed ???  $184EDF40xx8FF00 - Outside Temp ?";
CM_ BO_ 825 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $F0F0 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: $F0F0";
CM_ BO_ 826 "Cabin Temperature  $xxxx??7F7F7F7F7F - Cabin Temp ((($value / 100) - 40) * (5 / 9) + 32)  $????xx7F7F7F7F7F - Status bitmap ?";
CM_ BO_ 827 "UNKNOWN  changing variables – doesn’t seem like temperature";
CM_ BO_ 828 "UNKNOWN  Changes in second through fourth bytes. Assuming two words, starting at the first byte?";
CM_ BO_ 832 "VEHICLE ADJUSTED SPEED / GEAR (AUTO)  $ffffxx00???????? - current gear  Gear values include: f=offline, d=park, b=reverse, 0=neutral,  values 1 through 8 are the current gear, regardless of if they were manually selected or were selected by the automatic transmission  $ffff??00xxxxxx?? - bitmap (sparse) $ffff??00??????xx – speed (MPH)  The speed shown at this location is the speed that's shown on the dash, which is a GPS-adjusted speed value. Even if the vehicle's tire size is incorrectly set in";
CM_ BO_ 834 "SPECIAL HVAC CONTROLS  $0000000400 sync driver/passenger temps $8000000000 max ac setting";
CM_ BO_ 846 "UNKNOWN REMOTE START?  Fifth and six bytes change during handover from remote start to local run.";
CM_ BO_ 848 "DEPENDABLE TIME, DATE AND BUS ID  xx?????????????? -- seconds ??xx???????????? -- minutes ????xx?????????? -- hours ??????xxxx?????? -- year ??????????xx???? -- month ????????????xx?? -- day ??????????????01 -- can-ihs identifier  the last byte is different from this same message on the other bus.";
